<h2>What is Debian?</h2>
<ul class="slide">
  <li>Linux is just the kernel of your operating system.</li>
  <li>You need a lot of applications around.</li>
  <li>Those collections of software around the Linux kernel is called distribution.</li>
  <li>Companies who build such distributions are called distributors.</li>
  <li>They make money by selling their distribution in boxes, doing support and training.</li>
  <li>You might know Mandrake, Red Hat, Suse and others.</li>
  <li>Debian is just one of them.</li>
</ul>
